{@--2@} ({%a%}) To go
beyond, exceed (<ab>fig.</ab> also);  
{#vAgviBavAtivfttaM AcAryakaM#} <ls>Māl. 1. 26</ls> 
exceeding or transcending the powers of
speech, indescribable;  
{#mukulAvasTAmativfttezu taMqulezu#} <ls>Dk. 132</ls>; {#kA te stutiH#}
{#stutipaTAdativfttaDAmnaH#} <ls>Mv. 4. 29</ls>
transcending praise. ({%b%}) To offend,
overstep, transgress, violate;  
{#yosyAH SAsanamativartate#} <ls>Dk. 167</ls>;  
{#kotivartate dEvaM#} <ls n="Dk.">51</ls> who can transgress the
decrees of Fate? {#konyo jIvitukAmo#}
{#devasya SAsanamativarteta#} <ls>Mu. 3</ls>, <ls>Śi. 6. 19.</ls>
({%c%}) To neglect, omit, let slip. ({%d%})
To have no regard to, disregard,
slight; offend (especially by 
unfaithfulness), injure; {#SapaTaSatAtivartI#}
<ls>Dk. 62</ls> disregarding; {#ftusnAtAM#} 
{#satIM BAryAM… ativarteta duzwAtmA; yaTAhaM#} 
{#karmaRAvAcA SarIreRa ca rAGavaM . satataM nAtivarteya#}
<ls>Rām.</ls>; {#apatyaloBAdyAtu#} 
{#strIBartAramativartate#} <ls>Ms. 5. 161.</ls>

{@--3@} ({%a%}) To surpass, excel;
{#manuzyasaMKyAmativartituM vA#} <ls>Ki. 3. 40</ls>,  
<ls>Śi. 14. 59</ls>; {#bAMDavasnehaM rAjyaloBo'tivartate#}  
<ls>Ks. 41. 40</ls> to outweigh, preponderate. ({%b%}) To
overcome, subdue, vanquish, get the
better of; get over, escape or get
loose from; {#asADyAnativartaMte pramehA#} 
{#rajanIM yaTA#} <ls>Suśr.</ls>; {#kimAcAraH kaTaM#} 
{#cEtAMstrIn guRAnativartate#} <ls>Bg. 14. 21</ls> transcend
these three qualities; {#dEvaM pOruzeRa#}
<ls>Mb.</ls>, <ls>Dk. 73</ls>, <ls>Ks. 121. 67.</ls>

